# lfo: `taptempo` sets the LFO frequency from the interval between input clock
# edges (basics.md 3.3: two edges suffice; the last three are averaged; before
# any measurement the preset is 0.5 s = 2 Hz). Here we also patch `sync` to the
# same clock so phase is deterministic (taptempo alone does NOT sync phase,
# per basics.md), letting us read the frequency off the sawtooth ramp.
#
# Clock on I1: single-tick pulses at ticks 100, 1600, 3100 (interval 1500 ticks
# = 0.25 s at tickrate 6000 -> 4 Hz). After the 2nd edge the measured frequency
# is 4 Hz, so between edges the sawtooth ramps 0->~1 over 1500 ticks.
tickrate 6000
patch <<<
[lfo]
    hz       = 1
    taptempo = I1
    sync     = I1
    sawtooth = O1
>>>

@100  set I1 1
@101  set I1 0
@1600 set I1 1
@1601 set I1 0
@3100 set I1 1
@3101 set I1 0

# After edge 2 (tick 1600, phase reset to 0), measured freq = 4 Hz.
@1975 expect O1 0.25 tol 2e-3   # 375 ticks after reset -> phase 0.25
@2350 expect O1 0.5  tol 2e-3   # 750 ticks -> phase 0.5
@2725 expect O1 0.75 tol 2e-3   # 1125 ticks -> phase 0.75
